		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: The MITRE CVE dictionary describes this issue as: A heap-based buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Academy Software Foundation OpenEXR 2.3.0 in chunkOffsetReconstruction in ImfMultiPartInputFile.cpp that can cause a denial of service via a crafted EXR file. \n            STATEMENT: This flaw is out of support scope for OpenEXR as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6 and 7. For more information on Red Hat Enterprise Linux support scope, please see https://access.redhat.com/support/policy/updates/errata/ .",
